Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells consisting of Ni support, a screen-printed Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta anode functional layer, aerosol-deposited dense (La, Sr)(Ga, Mg)O3-delta electrolyte, and an aerosol-deposited porous (La, Sr)(Co, Fe)O3-delta cathode were fabricated and characterized.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of (La, Sr)(Ga, Mg)O3-δ electrolyte-based solid oxide fuel cells on Ni-support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: Both electrolyte and the cathode maintained good adhesion after electrochemical test of the cell at 750 degrees C, after the composition of anode functional layer was optimized.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of (La, Sr)(Ga, Mg)O3-δ electrolyte-based solid oxide fuel cells on Ni-support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: Microstructural analysis of powders and deposited films of electrolyte and cathode layers is presented.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of (La, Sr)(Ga, Mg)O3-δ electrolyte-based solid oxide fuel cells on Ni-support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: Maximum power density of 0.79 W/cm(2) was achieved at 750 degrees C. (C) 2013
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of (La, Sr)(Ga, Mg)O3-δ electrolyte-based solid oxide fuel cells on Ni-support by aerosol deposition
